Description: Egypt, view of temple of Philae. Partly submerged in River Nile. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Temple ruins were moved when area was submerged by Aswan Dam. The large structures are pylons [entrances]. J M Hudson, 27/01/1997. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
